{
  "stem": "20684.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[EXHALES] That's the last time I saw my father alive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went back--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A few times, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But not that often because he was in hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that's the last time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went back to-- to them, to the partisans, and we spent the next few months mainly in hiding because it was very dangerous to-- to-- there were lots of Germans coming there to be around.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we didn't do much killing, we were just hiding most of the time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But in April, that went shortly after that episode, about a month or so later, I was given what has become-- what has been my greatest present ever in my life, and I was given a bread, a whole bread.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's called the-- one of those peasant bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's black and it's hard and it's-- and it's heavy and it's got lots of sawdust, very little wheat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But anyhow, it was good.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, that bread was mine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I put the bread inside my shirt and I scratched on it right up till the Russians came over, which was from April till about August.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "For about three or four months I was scratching on that bread.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was my bread, my bread.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that stage, we were looking-- oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We eat whatever we can.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, in the forest it was like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, the law was basically if it's-- if it's small and you can catch it, you eat it and keep quiet about it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If it's big, you don't catch it, you keep away from it because it might eat you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So you keep away from bears and things like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm not stupid enough to grab them or wolves or things.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
